{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So today, I want us to reflect"},{"time":2000,"text":"on the demise of guys."},{"time":4000,"text":"Guys are flaming out academically;"},{"time":6000,"text":"they're wiping out socially with girls"},{"time":8000,"text":"and sexually with women."},{"time":10000,"text":"Other than that, there's not much of a problem."},{"time":13000,"text":"So what's the data?"},{"time":15000,"text":"So the data on dropping out is amazing."},{"time":17000,"text":"Boys are 30 percent more likely than girls"},{"time":19000,"text":"to drop out of school."},{"time":21000,"text":"In Canada, five boys drop out for every three girls."},{"time":24000,"text":"Girls outperform boys now at every level,"},{"time":26000,"text":"from elementary school to graduate school."},{"time":28000,"text":"There's a 10 percent differential"},{"time":30000,"text":"between getting BA's and all graduate programs,"},{"time":33000,"text":"with guys falling behind girls."},{"time":36000,"text":"Two-thirds of all students in special ed. remedial programs are guys."},{"time":40000,"text":"And as you all know,"},{"time":42000,"text":"boys are five times more likely than girls"},{"time":44000,"text":"to be labeled as having attention deficit disorder --"},{"time":46000,"text":"and therefore we drug them with Ritalin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"What's the evidence of wiping out?"},{"time":51000,"text":"First, it's a new fear of intimacy."},{"time":53000,"text":"Intimacy means physical, emotional connection"},{"time":56000,"text":"with somebody else --"},{"time":58000,"text":"and especially with somebody of the opposite sex"},{"time":61000,"text":"who gives off ambiguous, contradictory,"},{"time":63000,"text":"phosphorescent signals."},{"time":65000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":69000,"text":"And every year there's research done"},{"time":71000,"text":"on self-reported shyness among college students."},{"time":74000,"text":"And we're seeing a steady increase among males."},{"time":76000,"text":"And this is two kinds."},{"time":78000,"text":"It's a social awkwardness."},{"time":80000,"text":"The old shyness was a fear of rejection."},{"time":82000,"text":"It's a social awkwardness like you're a stranger in a foreign land."},{"time":84000,"text":"They don't know what to say, they don't know what to do,"},{"time":87000,"text":"especially one-on-one [with the] opposite sex."},{"time":90000,"text":"They don't know the language of face contact,"},{"time":93000,"text":"the non-verbal and verbal set of rules"},{"time":95000,"text":"that enable you to comfortably talk to somebody else,"},{"time":98000,"text":"listen to somebody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"There's something I'm developing here called social intensity syndrome,"},{"time":103000,"text":"which tries to account for why guys really prefer"},{"time":105000,"text":"male bonding over female mating."},{"time":108000,"text":"It turns out, from earliest childhood,"},{"time":110000,"text":"boys, and then men,"},{"time":112000,"text":"prefer the company of guys --"},{"time":114000,"text":"physical company."},{"time":116000,"text":"And there's actually a cortical arousal we're looking at,"},{"time":119000,"text":"because guys have been with guys"},{"time":121000,"text":"in teams, in clubs, in gangs, in fraternities,"},{"time":124000,"text":"especially in the military, and then in pubs."},{"time":127000,"text":"And this peaks at Super Bowl Sunday"},{"time":129000,"text":"when guys would rather be in a bar with strangers,"},{"time":132000,"text":"watching a totally overdressed Aaron Rodgers of the Green Bay Packers,"},{"time":136000,"text":"rather than Jennifer Lopez totally naked in the bedroom."},{"time":139000,"text":"The problem is they now prefer"},{"time":141000,"text":"[the] asynchronistic Internet world"},{"time":143000,"text":"to the spontaneous interaction"},{"time":145000,"text":"in social relationships."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"What are the causes? Well, it's an unintended consequence."},{"time":150000,"text":"I think it's excessive Internet use in general, excessive video gaming,"},{"time":153000,"text":"excessive new access to pornography."},{"time":157000,"text":"The problem is these are arousal addictions."},{"time":160000,"text":"Drug addiction, you simply want more."},{"time":162000,"text":"Arousal addiction, you want different."},{"time":164000,"text":"Drugs, you want more of the same -- different."},{"time":166000,"text":"So you need the novelty in order for the arousal to be sustained."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"And the problem is the industry is supplying it."},{"time":172000,"text":"Jane McGonigal told us last year"},{"time":174000,"text":"that by the time a boy is 21,"},{"time":176000,"text":"he's played 10,000 hours of video games,"},{"time":178000,"text":"most of that in isolation."},{"time":180000,"text":"As you remember, Cindy Gallop said"},{"time":182000,"text":"men don't know the difference"},{"time":185000,"text":"between making love and doing porn."},{"time":187000,"text":"The average boy now watches 50 porn video clips a week."},{"time":190000,"text":"And there's some guy watching a hundred, obviously."},{"time":193000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":195000,"text":"And the porn industry is the fastest growing industry in America --"},{"time":198000,"text":"15 billion annually."},{"time":200000,"text":"For every 400 movies made in Hollywood,"},{"time":202000,"text":"there are 11,000 now made porn videos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"So the effect, very quickly,"},{"time":207000,"text":"is it's a new kind of arousal."},{"time":209000,"text":"Boys' brains are being digitally rewired in a totally new way"},{"time":212000,"text":"for change, novelty, excitement and constant arousal."},{"time":215000,"text":"That means they're totally out of sync in traditional classes,"},{"time":218000,"text":"which are analog, static, interactively passive."},{"time":220000,"text":"They're also totally out of sync"},{"time":222000,"text":"in romantic relationships,"},{"time":224000,"text":"which build gradually and subtly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"So what's the solution? It's not my job."},{"time":228000,"text":"I'm here to alarm. It's your job to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"But who should care? The only people who should care about this"},{"time":238000,"text":"is parents of boys and girls,"},{"time":240000,"text":"educators, gamers, filmmakers"},{"time":242000,"text":"and women who would like a real man"},{"time":244000,"text":"who they can talk to, who can dance,"},{"time":246000,"text":"who can make love slowly"},{"time":248000,"text":"and contribute to the evolutionary pressures"},{"time":250000,"text":"to keep our species above banana slugs."},{"time":253000,"text":"No offense to banana slug owners. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}